Botswana’s Economy to Expand 10-12% This Year, Central Bank's Mohohlo Says

-- B y   J e r r y   B u n g u
-- 
2011-03-23T08:48:39Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-23/botswana-s-economy-to-expand-10-12-this-year-central-bank-s-mohohlo-says.html
Botswana’s economy may expand by 10
percent to 12 percent this year on a recovery in world diamond
demand, said Linah Mohohlo, the governor of the country’s
central bank.  Mohohlo was speaking in the capital, Gaborone, at a
briefing for a business delegation from  Sweden .  The southern African nation’s economy grew by 10.7 percent
in 2010 on a 21.7 percent expansion in the  mining industry ,
Finance Minister Kenneth Matambo said on Feb. 7.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Jerry Bungu in Gaborone at 
 jbungu@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
